New `sendCaptureEvent`:

```java
private void sendCaptureEvent(String sourceApp, String text, int eventType) {
    executor.execute(() -> {
        try {
            JSONObject payload = new JSONObject();
            payload.put("source_app", sourceApp);
            payload.put("text", text);
            payload.put("event_type", eventType);
            payload.put("timestamp", System.currentTimeMillis());

            File logFile = getLogFile();
            if (logFile == null) {
                Log.e(TAG, "No log file directory available");
                return;
            }

            try (FileWriter fw = new FileWriter(logFile, true);
                 BufferedWriter bw = new BufferedWriter(fw)) {
                bw.write(payload.toString());
                bw.newLine();
            }
        } catch (Exception e) {
            Log.e(TAG, "Failed to log capture event", e);
        }
    });
}
```

Where it writes:

- File path: **app-specific external files dir**, usually  
  `Android/data/com.udacapp.udac/files/udac_continuity_log.jsonl`  

No permissions needed, no Play Protect storage drama, still inspectable with the right tools.

Each line is a JSON object like:

```json
